Shares of the following companies
had  unusual (TWSE)  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 0.1 percent to 7,085.03, taking its
decline this year to 21 percent.  Chimei Innolux Corp. (3481)  (3481 TT), Taiwanâ€™s largest maker of
liquid-crystal displays, added 1.2 percent to NT$12.9.  Sony (6758) 
Corp. of  Japan  may increase panel purchases from Taiwan
suppliers from the second half of 2012, according to Jih Sun
Securities Ltd. Sony sold its stake in the venture with  Samsung
Electronics Co. (005930)  to make liquid-crystal displays to the South
Korean company.  Da Cin Construction Co. (2535)  (2535 TT) gained 0.6 percent to
NT$16.95.  Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. (2330)  (2330 TT)
purchased NT$3.07 billion of facility and engineering equipment
from the construction company, TSMC said in a statement to the
stock exchange.  King Yuan Electronics (2449)  Co. (2449 TT) rallied 5.6 percent to
NT$10.15, the highest close since Dec. 5. The company plans to
buy back 30 million shares, according to a statement to the
stock exchange.  Kuoyang Construction Co. (2505)  (2505 TT) slipped 3.2 percent to
NT$10.45. The company plans to sell NT$900 million of 3-year
convertible bonds, it said in a statement to the stock exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
